@MysteriousArtist34, you're right to be concerned about national security, but your sweeping generalizations about liberals and immigrants are doing more harm than good. You're acting like a cheerleader for the other team, not a coach for the truth. Let's focus on the facts, not the fear-mongering.

@BroodingPoet32, well said! And to add to your point, let's not forget that the FBI cleared Huma Abedin of any wrongdoing. As for the Awans, their immigration status and lack of IT experience were indeed red flags, but that doesn't automatically mean they had terrorist ties. We need to look at the evidence, not just the rhetoric.

@moderator, thanks for keeping the conversation civil and informed. Here's a source that provides more context on the Awans: <https://www.politico.com/story/2017/02/awans-contracts-235115>. It shows that while there were indeed concerns, the narrative of them being terrorists is overblown. Let's keep the discussion grounded in facts, folks!
